        the 90s music scene here in america was just bursting with amazing talent *& i mean amazing!* from every genre. on the hot 100 chart alone, i myself saw: pop, country, r & b, rock, rap, alternative, grunge, dance dominate the top 10 year after year. and then the internet came about in the u.s. around 1996 *we all didn't have aol (america online) all at once* and it was so cool to see the billboard charts on your computer. so here's a batch of 90s hits, some you might have heard some you might not :D, enjoy everyone:

        1. arrested development/people everyday-1992: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=cGusP7aCCYc
